::DarkMouse::

She watched him walk past her and not even seem to notice her.  She 
sat in the chair at the console.  She faced the computer, but wasn't 
looking at it. She picked up her pet and placed it in her lap. She 
petted her pet rat.  She was wishing he hadn't restored her memory.  
Now she remembered why she broke the box in the first place.
And she knew that when he answered her in the forest clearing, he was 
speaking truely at her.  She knew now that she was nothing to him.
She just sat there with a blank expression on her face.
